issue.title: error undefined reference to `OrtGetApi' in C++ when run on g++

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
Hi, I'm using onnx runtime to load onnx in C++. I have installed docker from source. However, when i run CXX_Api_Sample.cpp file by g++ then facing the following error:
`/onnxruntime/csharp/test/Microsoft.ML.OnnxRuntime.EndToEndTests.Capi/CXX_Api_Sample.cpp: In function 'int main(int, char**)':
/onnxruntime/csharp/test/Microsoft.ML.OnnxRuntime.EndToEndTests.Capi/CXX_Api_Sample.cpp:60:28: warning: comparison between signed and unsigned integer expressions [-Wsign-compare]
   for (signed int i = 0; i < num_input_nodes; i++) {
                            ^
/onnxruntime/csharp/test/Microsoft.ML.OnnxRuntime.EndToEndTests.Capi/CXX_Api_Sample.cpp:76:24: warning: comparison between signed and unsigned integer expressions [-Wsign-compare]
     for ( int j = 0; j < input_node_dims.size(); j++)
                        ^
/tmp/cccNgi5D.o: In function __static_initialization_and_destruction_0(int, int)':
CXX_Api_Sample.cpp:(.text+0x892): undefined reference to OrtGetApi'
collect2: error: ld returned 1 exit status
`

I'm new, because I don't know this error is from where. I think that this line give out this error. But i'm not sure.
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/74517bb7425b52fd15fef5cf4d4f476c1987e764/csharp/test/Microsoft.ML.OnnxRuntime.EndToEndTests.Capi/CXX_Api_Sample.cpp#L9


Help me solve it , thanks so much.

issue.title: Error in c_cxx samples: error: ‘OrtGetApi’ was not declared in this scope

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
I follow [this](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/rel-1.3.0/BUILD.md#Build-ONNX-Runtime-Server-on-Linux) to build onnxruntime from source.

After that I compile the CXX_Api_Sample.cpp 

First, I got the error message 

In function __static_initialization_and_destruction_0(int, int)':
CXX_Api_Sample.cpp:(.text+0x8a1): undefined reference to `OrtGetApiBase'
collect2: error: ld returned 1 exit status

I follow #1897 to solve the problem 
add this code 
`const OrtApi* Ort::g_api = OrtGetApi(ORT_API_VERSION);
`

And I got another error message 

CXX_Api_Sample.cpp:10:20: error: ‘Ort::g_api’ should have been declared inside ‘Ort’
 const OrtApi* Ort::g_api = OrtGetApi(ORT_API_VERSION);
                    ^
CXX_Api_Sample.cpp:10:53: error: ‘OrtGetApi’ was not declared in this scope
 const OrtApi* Ort::g_api = OrtGetApi(ORT_API_VERSION);

Could someone help me?
